text: Bought LongTong for myself and Mee Siam for my colleague. Very well cooked vegetables, rice cakes were soft and tasty. My colleague shared that the Mee Siam has a very nice fragrance in it. Both were delicious! Will return for more!

Surprised to find Indonesian Food at the Empress Market.  It serves a variety of noodle and rice dishes, and some ala carte side orders.

Tried the Mee Rebus, it's quite tasty and very generous serving for a very reasonable price.  The fried chicken side order looks yummy but did not try.  Maybe next time.

A mildly spiced soup base.
The assorted vegetables were cooked till soft (a bit too mushy for me). The sambal was sweet and spicy which when mixed, elevated the dish.

An assorted Malay dishes are available and the lady boss was friendly and courteous.
We wanted to try the Ah Ming wanton noodle but the queue and waiting time was too long. In the end tried Mee Rebus. Not bad. Big portion too.

I tried their nasi padang yesterday. I bought beef rendang, egg and sambal goreng. The price $5.00 is reasonably. But the food was disappointing. The rendang was tough. The sambal goreng is not too spicy...blunt. I can say I am very disappointed with the taste. Not returning back.
